00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.339
Now we've practiced making functions that can do three main things.

00:00:04.339 --> 00:00:06.125
One, they work is a black box,

00:00:06.125 --> 00:00:08.779
which means that they contain and execute multiple lines of

00:00:08.779 --> 00:00:11.924
code without you having to know what that code is.

00:00:11.925 --> 00:00:15.925
Two, they can take in data as arguments and work with that data.

00:00:15.925 --> 00:00:18.410
And three, they can return data and then

00:00:18.410 --> 00:00:22.019
their output can be treated just like you would treat any other variable.

00:00:22.019 --> 00:00:24.530
And the black box is often what makes functions so

00:00:24.530 --> 00:00:28.580
powerful because without having to know all the code inside a function,

00:00:28.579 --> 00:00:31.309
you employ all its code just by calling the function by

00:00:31.309 --> 00:00:34.579
name and giving it any parameters that it requires.

00:00:34.579 --> 00:00:36.559
This is especially useful whenever you want to use

00:00:36.560 --> 00:00:39.230
functions that someone else has written.

